  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a descriptive prospective community-based seroprevalence study.

      Primary objective:

        -  To determine the prevalence of specific antibodies (immunoglobulin G [IgG]) against
           dengue in healthy 5 to 10 year-old children in India.

      Secondary objectives:

        -  To determine the dengue virus serotype (DeNV-1,2,3 and /or 4) specific to the antibodies
           in positive (IgG) samples

        -  To estimate the prevalence of specific antibodies (IgG) against Japanese encephalitis in
           healthy 5 to 10 year-old children in India.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
